A Cloud Center of Excellence (CCoE) is a cross-functional team responsible for guiding cloud adoption across an organization. Instead of every department independently implementing cloud solutions, the CCoE establishes standards, governance, best practices, and architectural guidance.

Typical responsibilities include:

* Developing cloud standards
* Defining governance policies
* Supporting migration projects
* Promoting security best practices
* Training technical teams
* Monitoring cloud adoption progress

For example, a large financial institution may establish a CCoE to review cloud architectures before production deployment.

A real-life use case is organizations ensuring that cloud projects remain secure, compliant, and aligned with business objectives while encouraging innovation.
